This file describes how to use the CMake build system.

1) install CMake

(Windows specific)
if you are using Visual Studio under Windows, you need to execute vcvars32.bat
to set the necessary environment variables (look in the folder where Visual C is installed)

2) run cmake-gui
3) set "source code folder" to the folder projects/CMake
4) set "build folder" to the folder projects/CMake/build

(Windows specific)
download the dependencies and extract them in projects/CMake/dependencies
add a new path entry CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH set to projects/CMake/dependencies

5) hit configure
6) hit build
7) your projects are located in the build folder

For more detailed information, please refer to : http://sourceforge.net/apps/trac/orcc/wiki/OrccUserDocumentation